value.value: A potassium channel protein that is activated by sodium. A sodium-activated potassium channel enables the transmembrane transfer of potassium by a channel that opens in response to stimulus by a sodium ion or ions.

label.value: calcium- and sodium-activated potassium channel protein

value.value: A potassium channel protein that is activated either by calcium or by sodium.
A potassium channel protein that has inward rectifier potassium channel activity. An inwardly rectifying potassium channel is one where the inward flow of K+ ions exceeds the outward flow.

label.value: two P domain potassium channel protein

value.value: A potassium channel protein that is a translation product of any of the human KCNK1 through KCNK18 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.

A potassium channel protein that has voltage-gated potassium channel activity. A voltage-gated potassium channel enables the transmembrane transfer of a potassium ion by a voltage-gated channel. A voltage-gated channel enables the transmembrane transfer of a solute by a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

A voltage-gated ion channel protein that has potassium channel activity. A potassium channel enables the facilitated diffusion of a potassium ion (by an energy-independent process) involving passage through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel without evidence for a carrier-mediated mechanism.
A voltage-gated ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human RYR1, RYR2, or RYR3 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.

A voltage-gated ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human TRPC1, TRPM1, TRPV1, TRPA1, TRPP1 or TRPML1 gene, paralogs thereof, 1:1 orthologs thereof, a semi-ortholog thereof, or pro-orthologs thereof.

A voltage-gated ion channel protein that has voltage-gated calcium channel activity. A voltage-gated calcium channel enables the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a voltage-gated channel. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

A voltage-gated ion channel protein that has voltage-gated proton channel activity. A voltage-gated proton channel enables the transmembrane transfer of a proton by a voltage-gated channel. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

A voltage-gated ion channel protein that has voltage-gated sodium channel activity. A voltage-gated sodium channel enables the transmembrane transfer of a sodium ion by a voltage-gated channel. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.
A ligand-gated ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human HTR3A, HTR3B, HTR3C, HTR3D, or HTR3E genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.

A ligand-gated ion channel protein that has pH-gated monoatomic ion channel activity. A pH-gated ion channel opens when an extracellular proton has been bound by the channel complex, and enables the transmembrane transfer of a sodium ion.

definition.value: Category=family. Note: Acid-sensing ion channels operate as homo- or heterotrimers. [PRO:DAN, IUPHARfam:118]

value.value: A ligand-gated ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human SCNN1A, SCNN1B, SCNN1D, or SCNN1G genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.

A ligand-gated ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human GABRA1-6, GABRB1-3, GABRG1-3, GABRD, GABRE, GABRQ, GABRP, or GABRR1-3 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.
A ligand-gated ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human GLRA1, GLRA2, GLRA3, GLRA4, or GLRB genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.

A ligand-gated ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human GRIA1, GRIA2, GRIA3, GRIA4, GRID1, GRID2, GRIK1, GRIK2, GRIK3, GRIK4, GRIK5, GRIN1, GRIN2A, GRIN2B, GRIN2C, GRIN2D, GRIN3A, or GRIN3B genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.
A ligand-gated ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human ITPR1, ITPR2, or ITPR3 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.
A ligand-gated ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human CHRNA1-7, CHRNA9-10, CHRNB1-4, CHRNG, CHRND, or CHRNE genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.
A ligand-gated ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human P2RX1, P2RX2, P2RX3, P2RX4, P2RX5, P2RX6, or P2RX7 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.
An ion channel protein that has ligand-gated ion channel activity. The ligand-gated ion channel opens when a specific ligand has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts.

A channel protein that has water channel activity. A water channel enables facilitated diffusion of water (by an energy-independent process) by passage through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel without evidence for a carrier-mediated mechanism.

definition.value: Category=family. Note: Aquaporin channels operate as tetramers. [PRO:DAN, IUPHARfam:119]

value.value: A chloride channel protein that is a translation product of the human CLCN1 to CLCN7, CLCNKA, or CLCNKB genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human SMIM29 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A chloride channel protein that has intracellular calcium activated chloride channel activity. A calcium activated chloride channel enables the transmembrane transfer of chloride by a channel that opens in response to stimulus by a calcium ion or ions.
A protein that has channel activity. Channel proteins enable energy-independent facilitated diffusion, mediated by passage of a solute through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel.

A chloride channel protein that has volume-sensitive chloride channel activity. A volume regulated chloride channel enables the transmembrane transfer of a chloride ion in response to a change in cell volume.

An ion channel protein that has chloride channel activity. A chloride channel enables the facilitated diffusion of a chloride (by an energy-independent process) involving passage through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel without evidence for a carrier-mediated mechanism.

An ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human GJA1, GJA3 to GJA5, GJA7 to GJA10, GJA12, GJB1 to GJB7, GJC3, GJE1, or GJD2 to GJD4 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.

definition.value: Category=family. Note: Connexin proteins operate as homo- or heterohexamers. [PRO:DAN]

value.value: An ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human PANX1, PANX2, or PANX3 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.

definition.value: Category=family. Note: Pannexin proteins operate as multimers of six or more channel forming subunits. [PRO:DAN, PMID:22305965]

value.value: An ion channel protein that is either a connexin or pannexin protein.
An ion channel protein that is a translation product of the human PIEZO1 or PIEZO2 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.

definition.value: Category=family. Note: Piezo channels are mechanosensitive ion channels that operate as homotrimers. [PRO:DAN, PMID:29376828]

value.value: An activated TLR4 complex whose components are encoded in the genome of human.

value.value: A bicistronic molybdopterin synthase catalytic subunit/molybdopterin synthase sulfur carrier subunit that is encoded in the genome of zebrafish.

A protein that is a translation product of the monocistronic Escherichia coli K-12 moaE gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof, or is a translation product of some mRNA encoded by the bicistronic human MOCS2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof, that gives rise to a protein containing the MoaE (Pfam:PF02391) domain.

A protein that is a translation product of the monocistronic Escherichia coli K-12 moaD gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof, or is a translation product of some mRNA encoded by the bicistronic human MOCS2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof, that gives rise to a protein containing the ThiS (Pfam:PF02597) domain.
An interferon alpha that is encoded in the genome of human.
